items.name: Jingliu | Honkai Star Rail
items.description:
Hello...

This is a LoRA for Jingliu character from Honkai Star Rail, trained in Anythingv4.5 for 50 epochs with 101 images 1 repeat

tbh i train it for 50 epochs (x/y test). this one using the last epoch, if you guys want other epochs just lemme know..

its match the character pretty well with model like anything or , for more information you can see the image previews.

for the weight i recommended using around 0.6-1 (Recommended 0.8)

as for the trigger words, i think you can use (cut if not used)

jingliu, long hair, bangs, red eyes, dress, bare shoulders, jewelry, medium breasts, blue hair, grey hair, earrings, boots, black gloves, elbow gloves, chinese clothes, china dress, hair stick, detached sleeves, hair ornament,

i guess that is all, thanks you....

Edit:
So i forgot some images that i use for the preview using control net when looking for pose or propotions, Here some guide to use ControlNet

  • Go towards extensions tabs and install this extension, https://github.com/Mikubill/sd-webui-controlnet

  • Download ControlNet model (https://huggingface.co/lllyasviel/ControlNet/tree/main/models) (recomended the openpose one) and place it inside sd-webui-controlnet/models extension folder

  • After installing, a tab named Control Net should be appeared in txt2img or img2img

  • Open the tab and use this image as a guidelines, pretty much use openpose preprocessor and openpose model then place the image that you want to use inside the tab.

  • Sometimes this method not working, you can use openpose stickman instead, here my collection of openpose stickman (set preprocessor to none like this)

  • Then just generate images like usual, just leave the ControlNet enabled. the image should resemble the pose

items.name: Periwinkle
items.description:
What is Periwinkle?

Periwinkle is an anime model with a unique blend or aesthetic. A tool to assist artists and writers for creating illustration for graphic novels, manga, kids' book, promotional arts and more. I personally use this model for my works, which is well suited on one of my styles. Regarding text prompts, just be versatile and let your imagination flow. And, just like most models it also has few issues with the hands, which can be easily mitigated with this model's inpainting (download separately) or some embeddings. (I still have other models, for some specific arts, yet to be released. Your support will go a long way, and a cup of coffee will keep me awake for many nights. Thank you in advance!)

This version of Periwinkle does not include a VAE because the goal is for art versatility, wherein, you can use any VAE you like to produce unique aesthetics. Below are the recommended VAEs that you can use with this model to tweak a unique output.

kl-f8-anime2 VAE (for anime)

anything VAE aka orangemix VAE (for anime)

blessed VAE (for anime)

vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned (for realism)

Sample images above were created with simple text prompts around default settings. More detailed prompts will produce much better results. As for text prompts, just let your imagination flow. One thing to take note, adding keywords like realistic, realism, photorealism, photorealistic, hyperrealism, hyper-realistic etc., will make the image more real, and not including any word with real on them will make it look anime.

Settings:

Sampling Method: Euler (realistic) or Euler A (anime)

Sampling Steps: 20 to 30

Resolution: 512x512, 512x768, 768x512

CFG Scale: 4 to 7

Popular Embeddings Used (in the samples):

Easy Negative

Deep Negative

Bad artist Negative embedding

veryBadImageNegative

bad_prompt Negative Embedding

negative_hand Negative Embedding

EnvyBetterHands LoCon

Detail Tweaker LoRA

SXZ Vivid Darkness

Theovercomer8's Contrast Fix

Limitations:

Do use this model within the boundaries of legalities; do not use it to harm people and entities, or any illegal matters. Using this model means that you alone are responsible for any forms of consequences good or bad, and the author has no liabilities. We all know that AI models can produce both safe and unsafe images for work, so be very responsible. For all other matters do read the CreativeML-OpenRail-M license. Other than that, enjoy using this model and I hope this will help you in your endeavors as an artist.

Support:

First of all, thank you for patronizing this model; it means my efforts didn't go to waste. My goal is to produce more free tools not just for myself and my work, but for others too. Your generosity will go more than a mile. Also, as an artist, writer, programmer, and overall freelancer, I accept commission job. Thank you so much for your support!

Nizomi is a mysterious and enigmatic girl with a captivating presence. With her long, flowing hair that cascades down in a striking shade of greyish purple, she effortlessly stands out in any crowd. Often seen in her school uniform, she exudes an air of elegance and sophistication. Her grey jacket and pleated skirt, paired with a crisp white dress shirt, a black necktie, and black pantyhose, give her a distinctive and polished appearance.

One cannot help but notice Nizomi's physical features, as she possesses a curvaceous figure. Her large breasts and wide hips accentuate her feminine allure. Yet, despite the attention she may attract, she remains stoic and expressionless most of the time.

Nizomi's reserved nature adds to her air of mystery. She is a girl of few words, often preferring silence over idle chatter. Her quiet demeanor gives rise to numerous speculations about her thoughts and feelings, leaving those around her intrigued and curious.

Beneath her reserved exterior, Nizomi possesses a deep well of complexity and untold stories. Her presence commands attention, and those who take the time to unravel her layers may discover a fascinating and multi-faceted individual with hidden depths.

Nizomi's allure lies not only in her striking appearance but also in the enigma that surrounds her. She is a captivating enigma, inviting speculation and leaving others yearning to know more about the girl behind the expressionless facade.
